INSERT INTO `page` VALUES (960, NULL, NULL, NULL, 17, 8, 196, 'Enable/Disable Force Back To Source URI', '\n\n    \n##### Description\n\n- This Interface Is Used To Enable/Disable Force Back To Source URI\n\n##### Request URI\n- ` /api/v1/site/change-switch-status `\n  \n  \n##### Request Method\n- POST \n\n#### Request Head\n\n- greycdn-token: 1d2n3j9x-wjeg-469a-9a3b-033sd909qd91\n\n> *greycdn-token: This Is Using User Based API Token, API Token format as c6fb127e-3848-4sh2-98d9-cbe1238jdj44e5\n\n- User-Agent Greypanel-CDN-API-V2\n\n> *When Makaking Request，Its a Must To Provide UA Head For Identification and Its Also Required For Others API Requests, Otherwise Request Will Be Intercept.\n\n##### Parameter Description\n\n|Parameter|Required|Type|Description|\n|:----    |:---|:----- |-----   |\n|status  |Yes  |number |1/0 (Enable/Disable)    |\n|switchName  |Yes  |string |Switch Name    |\n\n#### Request Example \n\n``` \ncurl -X POST   \'http://api2.greypanel.com/api/v1/site/change-switch-status?uid=uid\' \n-H \"greycdn-token: 1d2n3j9x-wjeg-469a-9a3b-033sd909qd91\"\n-H \"User-Agent: Greypanel-CDN-API-V2\"     \n-d \'{\n  \"status\": 0,\n  \"switchName\": \"proxyUriSwitch\"\n}\'\n``` \n\n##### Response Example \n\n\n``` \n{\n  \"result\": {},\n  \"response\": \"success\",\n  \"message\": \"禁用成功\"\n}\n```\n\n', 6, 0, NULL, NULL, 2, 0);
INSERT INTO `page` VALUES (961, NULL, '2021-06-25 19:23:11', NULL, 25, 8, 0, 'PCRART Track System Portal', '# PCR/ART Track System Portal\n\n\n\nPCR/ART Track System Portal is web‐based application that designed and developed by **Greypanel Singapore**, help **SBM Offshore** to Track and Store their PCR/ART Test Results. It is associated with encrypted cloud based server and high availiablity database, which is able to receive and store the submitted personal test result via whatsapp, and submitted group test result via E-mails. It is also able to generate reports manually or by schedule. The Web portal is browsable by IE/Chrome/Firefox Safari from computer, phone or tablet, in other words, Users have instant access to PCR/ART Test Records wherever and whenever they want. \n\n\n\n##### Compatable with:\n\n+ MS IE/Edge\n+ Chrome\n+ Firefox\n+ Safari\n\n\n\n## Quick Start Guide\n\n\n\n### Portal Login\n\nThe interface is suitable for use on any computer and even your mobile/tablet devices. It provides a\nbasic, web‐based interface that allows you to use the core features efficiently, such as adding and\ndownloading files.\nLaunch your internet browser and browse to http://covidreport.greycdn.com\n\n\n<img src=\"/upload/60d00f7042912.jpg\" width = \"500\"  alt=\"LoginPage\" align=\"center\" border = \"5\" />\n\n\n###### Login Tips\n\n+ Username and password is created by portal administrators, User will need to obtain authentication from portal administrators in order to login;\n\n+ The Username(E-mail address) is not case sensitive; the password provided is case sensitive;\n\n+ You may change password after login portal; Your new password may be from 8 to 32 characters in length, must contain at least one alpha character, one numeric character, and one special character (e.g. !, @, #, etc.). The password is case sensitive;\n+ if you forget your Username or Password, please contact administrator or your superviser to retrieve your Username or reset your Password.\n\n\n\n### Getting Started\n\n\n\nOnce successfully login, **Test Records** Menu shall present to the web page. \n\nPortal Layouts consists of 2 main parts, **Feature Menu Panel** on the left and **Main Content Area** in the centre:\n\n\n\n<img src=\"/upload/60d00fbf89915.jpg\" width = \"500\"  alt=\"LoginPage\" align=\"center\" border = \"5\" />\n\n\nThree Key features are located under Feature Manu Panel, including:\n\n+ Test Records\n+ Staff List\n+ Admin Panel\n+ Change Password\n+ Logout\n\n\n\nUser is able to change passord from **Change Password** Menu. \n\n<img src=\"/upload/60d010516e82c.jpg\" width = \"600\"  alt=\"LoginPage\" align=\"center\" border = \"5\" />\n\n\n\n\nTo log out from the system, Click the **Logout** Menu.\n\n\n\n**Admin Panel** is only accesseble by User Right accociated with Admin Access, function will be explain later in this manual.\n\n\n\n### Test Records\n\nTest Records are displayed in table format, User is able to search test records by keys of Staff name, Identification/Passport Number, Contact, Test Type, Test Status, Latest PCR Test Date, Latest ART Test Date etc.\n\n(insert a screenshot)\n\n\n\nTest Records data are displayed as following format:\n\n| S/N  | NAME         | NRIC/FIN/PASSPORT | STATUS        | LATEST PCR  | LATEST ART  |     OPTIONS      |\n| ---- | ------------ | ----------------- | ------------- | ----------- | ----------- | :--------------: |\n| 1    | Thomas Bill  | S1234567M         | Normal        | 2021-May-20 | 2021-May-24 | Certificate/Edit |\n| 2    | Charles Beta | S1234568M         | PCR Required  | 2021-May-24 | 2021-May-18 | Certificate/Edit |\n| 3    | Alfa Cohn    | S1234569M         | ART Scheduled | 2021-May-28 | 2021-May-20 | Certificate/Edit |\n\n\n\nTest Record can by filtered by NAME, NRIC/FIN/PASSPORT,  CONTACT, STATUS, LATEST PCR Date or  LATEST ART Date .\n\n\n\n##### Test Record Status\n\nThere are 5 Status defined in the records, they are:\n\n+ Normal\n+ Positive\n+ PCR Required\n+ ART Scheduled\n+ ART Required\n\n<img src=\"/upload/60d0129dc48f4.jpg\" width = \"400\"  alt=\"LoginPage\" align=\"center\" border = \"5\" />\n\n\nEach status associated with different higntligh colours:\n\n\n| Status  | Colour Code  | Remark |\n| ------------ | ------------ |\n| Normal  |  No Colour <div style=\"\"></div>  | Completed Required Test, and permitted to work |\n| Positive  |   <div style=\"background: black; color: grey; padding: 5px;\">Black</div> |Test Result showing Positve in PCR or ART |\n| PCR Required |   <div style=\"background: red; color: grey; padding: 5px;\">Red</div> | PCR Test Needed, NOT Permit to work |\n| ART Scheduled |   <div style=\"background: yellow; color: grey; padding: 5px;\">Yellow</div> | Required to conduct ART Test, NOT Permit to work |\n\n\nStatus Logic is calculated base on give document:\n\n<img src=\"/upload/60d010e30808f.jpg\" width = \"800\"  alt=\"LoginPage\" align=\"center\" border = \"5\" />\n\n\nTwo feature buttons are placed on the top of this page, **Upload Information**  and **Download**.\n\n\n\n##### Upload Information\n\nPortal User can upload staff test result by clicking this button, fill up with required information to update the staff result. Required Information including:\n\n+ Select staff\n+ Select Test Date\n+ Seletct Test Type\n+ Select Test Result\n+ Upload Test Certificate\n\nas below figure:\n\n<img src=\"/upload/60d011a496378.jpg\" width = \"500\"  alt=\"LoginPage\" align=\"center\" border = \"5\" />\n\n\n\nSubmitted information will update in the database immediately.\n\n\n\n##### Download\n\nTest Records Table is available to download by clicking the **Download** button, a csv format file will downloaded to local device, and it is excutiable by MS-Office Excel.\n\n> Note: the download data can be filterred by search function.\n\n\n\n##### **Certificates and Edit**\n\nStaff Test Result can be view by clicking **Certificates** button in the table. Historical Test Result can be modify by clicking **Edit** button in the table.\n\n\n\n### Staff List\n\nStaff list is accessible by portal user to add, modify, delete staff. Staff list is display in table format as:\n\n| S/N  | Name | NRIC/FIN/PASSPORT | Status |\n| :--- | :--- | :---------------- | :----- |\n|      |      |                   |        |\n\nPortal provides 4 feature buttons to Add, Enable/Disable, and delete staff.\n\n\n\n<img src=\"/upload/60d011d548388.jpg\" width = \"800\"  alt=\"LoginPage\" align=\"center\" border = \"5\" />\n\n\n\n##### Add staff\n\nA few basic information is required to add new staff in the portal:\n\n+ S/N\n+ Name\n+ NRIC/FIN/PASSPORT\n+ Contact\n+ Gender\n+ Nationality\n+ Company\n+ Department\n\n> Note:\n>\n> Make sure contact is correctly\n\n\n\n\n\n### Admin Panel\n\n**Admin Panel** is only accesseble by User Right accociated with Admin Access.  Its 2 sub menus are **User Control** and **Message Logs**\n\n<img src=\"/upload/60d011f66d11d.jpg\" width = \"800\"  alt=\"LoginPage\" align=\"center\" border = \"5\" />\n\nIn this portal, 2 user types are defined to create a new portal user: **Admin** or **Normal**. The only different of the 2 types of users is that, Admin is granted permission to access **Admin Panel** while User is not. In this case, only admin is able to create, modify or delete portal users.\n\n<img src=\"/upload/60d0123decd89.jpg\" width = \"600\"  alt=\"LoginPage\" align=\"center\" border = \"5\" />\n\n\nIn User Control Menu, Portal Admin is able to create, modify or delete portal user, the new user can be granted with Admin Access Rights or User Access Rights. \n\n\n\n<img src=\"/upload/60d0125ac29e3.jpg\" width = \"400\"  alt=\"LoginPage\" align=\"center\" border = \"5\" />\n\n\nIn any case, portal admin is able to **Disable** or **Enable** a portal user, it gives the possiblility to restrict certain user from login to portal.\n\n\n\n### Test Result Submission\n\nThere are 3 options to upload PCR/ART Test Result to System: \n\n+ Manually upload through portal\n+ Via WhatsApp message\n+ Via E-mail\n\n\n\n#### Manually Upload through Portal\n\nPlease refer to portal manual of relevant section for details\n\n\n\n#### Via WhatsApp message\n\nRegisterred staffs are able to send PCR/ART Result to given WhatsApp Number **+65 12345678**. sender should follow a proper step in order to submit and upload test result successfully.\n\n1. Step1: send the test result text follow by format of \"YYYY-MMM-DD TestType TestResult\", for example: \n\n   \"2021-Jun-02 PCR N\"; TestType is PCR or ART; TestResult is P or N, P for Positive, N for Negative.\n\n> Note: \n>\n> + System will reply \"Please reply with correct data format: <yyyy-MMM-dd> <Test Type> <Test Result>, for example： 2021-Jun-02 PCR N; Test Type：PCR or ART; TestResult： N：negative，P：positive\" if sending Incorrect message format\n> + Please be aware that PCR result is usually received on the 2nd day of PCR Test, while ART Result can be received on the same day\n>\n> + Only sender number registerred in system is recogonized, otherwise sender will receive a message reply \"Your phone number is not registered in our contact list, please contact your supervisor for this issue\"\n> + System will ingore duplecated messages\n\n2. Step2: System will reply \"Please submit your test result snapshot\" once step1 is done correctly, and sender will need to send test result snapshot to the same whatsapp number. Uploaded snapshot will store in the database, available to review in the portal\n3. Step3: System will reply \"Your Test Result is received, YYYY-MMM-DD HH:mm:SS\". The whole test result submission process is completed at this stage\n\n> In any case of incorrect submissions, portal Admin is able to upload, modify, delete test result, filtered by Staff, TestType, Test Results. \n\n\n\n#### Via E-mail\n\nFor some cases, staffs have to approach to clinics for the PCR/ART Test, and the test result will be sent by the clinic via E-mail. \n\n1. In order to upload the result by reading E-mail contents, clinics need to send the result to given E-mail address: receiversbm@mail.com, followed by specific Subject Title: \n\n   <TestType> <yyyy-MMM-dd>, TestType can be PCR or ART\n\n   for example: ART 2021-May-20\n\n2. The test result should be attached in the E-mail, with specific format: \n\n   <NRIC/FIN/Passport>-<TestResult>.pdf, staff NIRC/FIN/Passport should be registred in staff list, TestResult is P or N, P for Positive, N for Negative.\n\n   for example: S1234567M-N.pdf\n\n3. Attachment will be stored as test result in the database, available to review in the portal\n\n> In any case of incorrect submissions, portal Admin is able to upload, modify, delete test result, filtered by Staff, TestType, Test Results. \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 99, 0, NULL, NULL, 2, 0);
